Course overview

Protect the house with earthing

START COURSE

Welcome to your Schneider Electric learning journey!


In this course, you will discover how to enable an electrically reliable and safe environment. By implementing effective earthing systems, you can provide a safe path for fault currents to flow, preventing electric shocks and minimizing the risk of electrical fires.


At the end of this course, you will be able to:

  • Define and determine the function of an earthing system
  • To differentiate types of earthing 
  • Learn the main steps to be followed for installing an earthing system 
  1. Introduction to electrical protection in the residential sector
  2. Practical case part 1
  3. Different types of earthing systems (TT, TN, IT)
  4. The different types of earthing pits
  5. What's earthing?
  6. What's bonding?
  7. Earthing, bonding or grounding? What's the difference?
  8. Practical case part 2
  9. Protective equipment
  10. Practical case part 3
  11. Installation of an earth pit: a step-by-step guide
  12. Earth pit resistance measurement
  13. Practical case part 4
  14. Test your skills
